# Email Configuration for Schwab Market Data Notifications
#
# 1. Copy this file to 'email_credentials.env'
# 2. Fill in your actual email credentials below
# 3. Update the recipient email addresses
# 4. Save the file (it will be automatically loaded by email_notifier.py)
# 5. Keep this file secure and never commit it to version control
# 6. Test configuration by running: python scheduled_coordinator.py SPY 5m --mode analysis

# === SMTP SERVER CONFIGURATION ===
# Gmail SMTP settings (most common)
SMTP_SERVER=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587

# Other common SMTP servers:
# Yahoo: smtp.mail.yahoo.com:587  
# Outlook: smtp-mail.outlook.com:587
# Custom: your-mail-server.com:587

# === SENDER CREDENTIALS ===
SENDER_EMAIL=your-email@gmail.com
SENDER_PASSWORD=your-app-password

# Note: For Gmail, use an "App Password" not your regular password
# Generate at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords

# === EMAIL RECIPIENTS ===
# Multiple recipients separated by commas
TO_EMAILS=recipient1@gmail.com,recipient2@yahoo.com

# Optional: CC recipients
CC_EMAILS=manager@company.com

# === EMAIL SETTINGS ===
# Custom sender name (optional)
SENDER_NAME=Schwab Trading Bot

# Subject prefix for easy filtering
SUBJECT_PREFIX=[SCHWAB]

# Email Notifications Include:
# - Position Opens: Technical conditions, entry price, market context
# - Position Closes: P&L analysis, exit price, profit/loss calculations
# - Real-time: Sent immediately when position changes occur
# - Multi-timeframe: Separate emails for 1m, 5m, and 15m signals

# Other Email Providers:
# For non-Gmail providers, you'll need to modify the SMTP settings in the code:
# - Outlook: smtp-mail.outlook.com:587
# - Yahoo: smtp.mail.yahoo.com:587
# - Custom: Update smtp_server and smtp_port in load_email_config() method 